    "body": "\n## Purpose\n\n#29424\n\nThis PR implements GPTQ support for MoE models with LoRA.\n\nPreviously, enabling LoRA on GPTQ-quantized MoE models would fail because `GPTQMarlinMoEMethod` did not explicitly support the modular GEMM interface required for LoRA. This PR enables the modular kernel path for GPTQ MoE when LoRA is active.\n\n### Key Changes\n\n1.  **Modular GEMM Selection (`vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/gptq_marlin.py`):**\n    *   Implemented `select_gemm_impl` in `GPTQMarlinMoEMethod` to allow switching to `MarlinExperts` or `BatchedMarlinExperts` when `is_lora_enabled` is true.\n    *   Added weight aliases (`w13_weight`, `w2_weight`) to ensure compatibility with the modular kernel's expected attribute names.\n\n    ```python\n    def select_gemm_impl(self, prepare_finalize, layer):\n        if not self.moe.is_lora_enabled:\n             raise NotImplementedError(...)\n        # Returns MarlinExperts verified for GPTQ\n        # ...\n    ```\n\n2.  **Configuration (`vllm/model_executor/layers/fused_moe/config.py`):**\n    *   Added `gptq_marlin_moe_quant_config` to generate the correct quantization descriptor for GPTQ Marlin MoE layers.\n\n## Test Plan\n\nVerified locally using a GPTQ-quantized MoE model with LoRA enabled.\n\n**Test Script:**\n\n```python\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport torch\nfrom vllm import LLM, SamplingParams\nfrom vllm.config import LoRAConfig\nimport vllm\n\nMODELS = {\n    \"gptq\": \"Qwen/Qwen1.5-MoE-A2.7B-Chat-GPTQ-Int4\"\n}\n\nMODEL_NAME = MODELS[\"gptq\"]\n\n# This is a dummy adapter I created.\nLORA_PATH = \"explore/moe_lora/lora_adapters/qwen1.5-moe-gptq-lora\"\n\nPROMPT = \"Explain the concept of mixture of experts in neural networks.\"\nMAX_TOKENS = 512\nTEMPERATURE = 0.0 \n\n\ndef main():\n    \n    lora_config = LoRAConfig(\n        max_loras=4,\n        max_lora_rank=16,\n        lora_dtype=torch.float16,\n    )\n    \n    try:\n        llm = LLM(\n            model=MODEL_NAME,\n            enable_lora=True,\n            max_loras=lora_config.max_loras,\n            max_lora_rank=lora_config.max_lora_rank,\n            tensor_parallel_size=1,\n            max_model_len=4096,\n            gpu_memory_utilization=0.90,\n            enforce_eager=True,\n            quantization=\"gptq_marlin\",\n            trust_remote_code=True,\n            kv_cache_dtype=\"auto\",\n            enable_prefix_caching=False,\n            enable_chunked_prefill=False\n        )\n                \n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"\\n[ERROR] Failed to load model: {e}\")\n        return 1\n    \n    sampling_params = SamplingParams(\n        temperature=TEMPERATURE,\n        max_tokens=MAX_TOKENS,\n        top_p=1.0,\n    )\n    \n    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*80)\n    print(\"RUNNING INFERENCE WITH LORA\")\n    print(\"=\"*80 + \"\\n\")\n    \n    try:\n        from vllm.lora.request import LoRARequest\n        \n        lora_request = LoRARequest(\n            lora_name=\"test_adapter\",\n            lora_int_id=8,\n            lora_path=LORA_PATH\n        )\n\n        outputs = llm.generate(\n            [PROMPT],\n            sampling_params,\n            lora_request=lora_request\n        )\n        \n        print(f\"Prompt: {PROMPT}\")\n        print(f\"Response: {outputs[0].outputs[0].text}\\n\")\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"\\n[ERROR] LoRA inference failed: {e}\\n\")\n        import traceback\n        traceback.print_exc()\n        return 1\n    \n    return 0\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n\n\n```\n\n**Test Result:**\n\n**Before this PR**\n```python\nNotImplementedError: GPTQMarlinMoEMethod must select appropriate gemm implementation based on the prepare_finalize\n```\n**After this PR**\n```python\nThe model loads successfully with LoRA adapters and performs inference and produces an output.\n```\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [x] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [x] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [x] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google\nDoc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
